Name: myofibrillar myopathy 1
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous

Name: myofibrillar myopathy 2
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the alpha-B-crystallin gene on chromosome 11q23.

Name: myofibrillar myopathy 3
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the TTID gene on chromosome 5q31.

Name: myofibrillar myopathy 4
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the ZASP gene on chromosome 10.

Name: myofibrillar myopathy 5
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the FLNC gene on chromosome 7q32.

Name: myofibrillar myopathy 6
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the BAG3 gene on chromosome 10q26.

Name: myofibrillar myopathy 7
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the KY gene on chromosome 3q22.

Name: myofibrillar myopathy 8
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that is characterized by childhood onset of slowly progressive proximal muscle weakness and atrophy resulting in increased falls

Name: fatal infantile hypertonic myofibrillar myopathy
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the CRYAB gene on chromosome 11q23.

Name: myofibrillar myopathy 9
Definition: A myofibrillar myopathy characterized by adult onset of slowly progressive muscle weakness involving the diaphragm and resulting in respiratory insufficiency that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the TTN gene on chromosome 2q31.
Synonym: proximal myopathy with early respiratory muscle involvement
